.TH onyx_config 1 "onyx_config, version <Version = onyx>"
.hy 1
.SH NAME
onyx_config - configuration helper for building with libonyx
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B onyx_config
.BR [ \-\-help ]
.BR [ \-\-prefix ]
.BR [ \-\-onyx\-path ]
.BR [ \-\-version ]
.BR [ \-\-features ]
.BR [ \-\-cppflags ]
.BR [ \-\-cflags ]
.BR [ \-\-ldflags ]
.BR [ \-\-libs ]
.SH DESCRIPTION
The
.B onyx_config
program is a script that aids in building programs with libonyx.
.SS Command line flags:
.IP \-\-help
Display usage information and exit.
.IP \-\-prefix
Display the installation prefix.
.IP \-\-onyx\-path
Display the absolute path to the onyx binary.
.IP \-\-version
Display the release version.
.IP \-\-features
Display a space-separated list of the features built into the Onyx interpreter.
.IP \-\-cppflags
Display the C preprocessor flags.
.IP \-\-cflags
Display the C compiler flags.
.IP \-\-ldflags
Display the library linker flags.
.IP \-\-libs
Display the libaries to link against.
.SH FILES
@prefix@/share/onyx/doc/html/onyx.html
.br
